<subSubSection id="C34219B3DD1DFFEF43D1FE45FBFEED9F" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE74A38DD1DFFEF43D1FE45FBFEED9F" blockId="1.[151,1436,152,940]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis id="B92C962ADD1DFFEF43D1FE45FEB1EC3A" bold="true" box="[199,309,498,521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC937C9DD1DFFEF422DFE45FE4EEC3A" box="[315,458,498,521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" refId="ref1039" refString="Evans, W. H. (1949) A catalogue of the Hesperiidae from Europe, Asia &amp; Australia in the British Museum (Natural History). The British Museum, London, 502 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 105941" type="book">Evans (1949)</bibRefCitation>
recorded one male 
<taxonomicName id="4C5831BBDD1DFFEF418DFE46FCB7EC3A" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1882" box="[667,819,497,521]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Halpe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sikkima">
<emphasis id="B92C962ADD1DFFEF418DFE46FCB7EC3A" box="[667,819,497,521]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Halpe sikkima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion id="499C84DADD1DFFEF4062FE45FC40EC3A" box="[884,964,498,521]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Hainan</collectingRegion>
. Since then, no more material of this species has been collected from this place again, although field surveys have been carried out on the island repeatedly, and a number of hesperiid species have been published as new to science (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC937C9DD1DFFEF4062FD8FFC6BEC7C" box="[884,1007,568,591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" refId="ref887" refString="Chou, I. (Ed.) (1994) Monographia Rhopalocerorum Sinensium. Henan Scientific and Technological Publishing House, Zhengzhou, 854 pp." type="book">Chou 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC937C9DD1DFFEF40EDFD8FFB28EC7C" box="[1019,1196,567,591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" refId="ref1139" refString="Fan, X. L., Wang, M. &amp; Zeng, L. (2007 a) The genus Idmon de Niceville (Lepidoptera: Hesperiidae) from China, withdescription of two new species. Zootaxa, 1510, 57 - 62." type="journal article">
Fan 
<emphasis id="B92C962ADD1DFFEF473CFD8FFBDDEC7C" box="[1066,1113,567,591]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">et al</emphasis>
. 2007a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC937C9DD1DFFEF47A1FD8FFAEDEC7C" box="[1207,1385,567,591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" refId="ref1186" refString="Fan, X. L., Wang, M., Chen, L. S. &amp; Zeng, L. (2007 b) The genus Zographetus Watson (Lepidoptera: Hesperiidae) in China, with the description of two new species. Entomological News, 118 (3), 296 - 302." type="journal article">
Fan 
<emphasis id="B92C962ADD1DFFEF47F0FD8FFA90EC7C" box="[1254,1300,567,591]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">et al</emphasis>
. 2007b
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC937C9DD1DFFEF4662FD8FFEB6EC42" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" refId="ref1091" refString="Fan, X. L. &amp; Chiba, H. (2008) A new species of the genus Hyarotis Moore (Lepidoptera: Hesperiidae) from China. Journal of South China Agricultural University, 29 (2), 74 - 75, 85." type="journal article">Fan &amp; Chiba 2008</bibRefCitation>
) or discovered as new records to the skipper fauna of 
<collectingCountry id="F34F0AA8DD1DFFEF4094FDEDFC46EC42" box="[898,962,602,625]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC937C9DD1DFFEF40C7FDEDFBFEEC42" box="[977,1146,601,625]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" refId="ref1245" refString="Fan, X. L., Huang, G. H., Wang, M., Wang, C. D. &amp; Su, W. B. (2003) A newly recorded genus and species of the skippers from China (Lepidoptera: Hesperiidae). Journal of South China Agricultural University, Natural Science Edition, 24 (4), 56 - 57." type="journal article">
Fan 
<emphasis id="B92C962ADD1DFFEF4715FDEDFBB6EC42" box="[1027,1074,601,625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC937C9DD1DFFEF4790FDEDFAADEC42" box="[1158,1321,601,625]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" refId="ref1317" refString="Fei, W., Huang, Z. F., Chiba, H. &amp; Fan, X. L. (2015) Capila lidderdali (Elwes, 1888), a newly recorded skipper from China (Lepidoptera: Hesperiidae). Journal of Environmental Entomology, 37 (1), 184 - 186." type="journal article">
Fei 
<emphasis id="B92C962ADD1DFFEF47A7FDEDFB64EC42" box="[1201,1248,601,625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). In recent literature specializing in the fauna of 
<collectingRegion id="499C84DADD1DFFEF4135FDCAFDF4ECA7" box="[547,624,637,660]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Hainan</collectingRegion>
skippers (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC937C9DD1DFFEF401DFDCAFC40ECA7" box="[779,964,637,660]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" refId="ref1418" refString="Gu, M. B. &amp; Chen, P. Z. (1997) Butterflies in Hainan Island. China Forestry Publishing House, Beijing, 355 pp." type="book">Gu &amp; Chen 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC937C9DD1DFFEF40D8FDCAFBA9ECA7" box="[974,1069,637,660]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" refId="ref1377" refString="Gu, M. B. (2002) Lepidoptera: Rhopalocera. In: Huang F. S. (Ed.), Forest Insects of Hainan. Science Press, Beijing, pp. 654 - 716." type="book chapter">Gu 2002</bibRefCitation>
; Chiba 2008), this species was not included. Thus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5831BBDD1DFFEF4244FD17FE4FEC84" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1882" box="[338,459,671,695]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Halpe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sikkima">
<emphasis id="B92C962ADD1DFFEF4244FD17FE4FEC84" box="[338,459,671,695]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">H. sikkima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remained a mysterious species in 
<collectingRegion id="499C84DADD1DFFEF407EFD17FC3CEC84" box="[872,952,672,695]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Hainan</collectingRegion>
, and its occurrence on the island needed reconfirmation. During a collecting trip at Wuzhishan (
<figureCitation id="136356BDDD1DFFEF41C8FD75FC99ECEA" box="[734,797,706,729]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1985,2007]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,226,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,226,1934]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 3. Landscape of Wuzhishan, Hainan, China. Photographed by Guoxi Xue." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1438063/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) in 2015, a male 
<taxonomicName id="4C5831BBDD1DFFEF40C0FD75FBCCECEA" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1882" box="[982,1096,705,729]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Halpe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sikkima">
<emphasis id="B92C962ADD1DFFEF40C0FD75FBCCECEA" box="[982,1096,705,729]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">H. sikkima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was captured by the first author of the present paper, representing the second specimen of this species from the island. Considering the figures and descriptions of the male genitalia in literature which are not complete and precise enough (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC937C9DD1DFFEF4785FCBFFA9DED2C" box="[1171,1305,776,799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" refId="ref1039" refString="Evans, W. H. (1949) A catalogue of the Hesperiidae from Europe, Asia &amp; Australia in the British Museum (Natural History). The British Museum, London, 502 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 105941" type="book">Evans 1949</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC937C9DD1DFFEF463EFCBFFF4BED72" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" refId="ref1525" refString="Maruyama, K. (1991) Butterflies of Borneo. Vol. 2. No. 2. Hesperiidae. Tobishima Corporation, Tokyo, 77 pp., 39 pls." type="book">Maruyama 1991</bibRefCitation>
), illustrations and a re-description are provided in this paper. 
<collectionCode id="ED49D2FDDD1DFFEF4086FC9DFC4EED72" box="[912,970,810,833]" country="Australia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" name="Department of Natural Resources, Environment, The Arts and Sport" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">DNA</collectionCode>
was extracted from one leg of the dried specimen using DNeasy 
<emphasis id="B92C962ADD1DFFEF428DFCFAFE22ED69" box="[411,422,845,858]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Â®</emphasis>
Blood and Tissue Kit (Qiagen, 
<collectingCountry id="F34F0AA8DD1DFFEF4016FCE7FCECED54" box="[768,872,848,871]" name="Germany" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Germany</collectingCountry>
). The 
<collectionCode id="ED49D2FDDD1DFFEF40BAFCE7FC5EED54" box="[940,986,848,871]" country="Portugal" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" name="University of Coimbra Botany Department" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">COI</collectionCode>
gene was amplified by PCR as described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC937C9DD1DFFEF43ADFCC5FE3BEDBA" box="[187,447,881,905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" refId="ref1449" refString="Hajibabaei, M., Janzen, D. H., Burns, J. M., Hallwachs, W. &amp; Hebert, P. D. (2006) DNA barcodes distinguish species of tropical Lepidoptera. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America, 103 (4), 968 - 971. https: // doi. org / 10.1073 / pnas. 0510466103" type="journal article">
Hajibabaei 
<emphasis id="B92C962ADD1DFFEF4221FCC5FEEBEDBA" box="[311,367,881,905]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
and then sequenced by Sangon biotech, 
<collectingRegion id="499C84DADD1DFFEF4094FCC5FC6CEDBA" box="[898,1000,882,905]" country="China" name="Shanghai" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Shanghai</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F34F0AA8DD1DFFEF40E3FCC5FBBCEDBA" box="[1013,1080,882,905]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">China</collectingCountry>
. The 
<collectionCode id="ED49D2FDDD1DFFEF4761FCC5FB21EDBA" box="[1143,1189,882,905]" country="Portugal" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" name="University of Coimbra Botany Department" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">COI</collectionCode>
sequence is published herein for the potential use in 
<collectionCode id="ED49D2FDDD1DFFEF42C1FC22FD95ED9F" box="[471,529,917,940]" country="Australia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" name="Department of Natural Resources, Environment, The Arts and Sport" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">DNA</collectionCode>
barcoding and a molecular phylogeny study in the future.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
